<P>
   NATO-NOTEBOOK (Washington) _ On Sunday morning, the daily NATO
briefing on Kosovo was followed by more of the silent motion
pictures of the latest Yugoslav bombings: mundane gray targets
loomed upward in the now familiar cross hairs, slowly rotating to
sudden explosive blots on the giant screen in the Reagan lobby.
Dozens of people moved past the highlight film, heedless as
commuters as they searched for fresh briefings and food and hints
of whatever was really happening. By Francis X. Clines.
</P>
<P>
   NATO-ASSESS (Washington) _ The timing could hardly have been
worse, and the commemoration of the 50th anniversary of the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization was largely obscured by savagery in
Kosovo and Colorado. By R.W. Apple Jr.
</P>
