   PARENTS-KIDS-DRUGS (Undated) _ New national survey shows
dramatic disconnect on the issue of parent-child communication
about drugs. Almost all parents surveyed say they've talked to
their children about drugs, but barely one-quarter of children
recall receiving any such guidance. By Christopher S. Wren.
