to us. Every one of them. We know these children. They are our sons
and daughters, our brothers and sisters. Every one of them is an
inestimable loss. And the loss is ours. (Kabat, Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ The dead had not been
removed from Columbine High School before easy explanations began
rolling in. It used to be enough for reporters to pronounce: ``the
gunman was described as a loner.'' These days, news consumers
demand more. We want to be reassured the murderers were not like
our kids. These were Nazis, black-fingernailed Goth-kids, white
punks on dope, anarchists, doomheads, gun-nuts and alienated
losers. Not like the kids we know. (Lane, Daytona Beach
News-Journal) MOVED
