<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Leaders work toward peace
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Russian officials are trying to mediate peace between
Yugoslavia and the North Atlantic Treaty Organization allies. A
former Russian premier met with Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic for nine hours last week in person, and continued to
negotiate by phone.
</P>
<P>
   The Russian peace plan calls for the withdrawal of NATO forces
massed at Yugoslav borders, a U.N.-led peace-keeping force in
Kosovo, a reduction in the number of Yugoslavian soldiers and
police officers in Kosovo and the return of refugees. NATO has
insisted it must lead any armed group in Kosovo to enforce a peace
agreement and says that Milosevic isn't willing to compromise
enough.
</P>
<P>
   Despite the discussions, NATO planes continued to bomb the
Yugoslavian capital and even Milosevic's house.
</P>
<P>
   Watch TV to lose weight
</P>
<P>
   Couch potatoes beware! If you want to watch TV, you may have to
work for it. Scientists trying to find ways to help kids slim down
experimented with a bicycle-powered TV. Kids had to pedal to create
the electricity to run the set.
</P>
<P>
   Ten overweight TV fans between the ages of 8 and 12 were
studied. Four were given stationary bikes not connected to the TV
and the other six had TVcycles. Those who pedaled to view burned
off more fat. They finished the study with 2 percentage points less
total body fat and 3 percentage points less fat on their legs than
the other kids. More than 13 percent of American kids ages 6 to 17
are overweight, and 55 percent of adults are too heavy.
</P>
<P>
   Catch 'N Sync, Spears performing live
</P>
<P>
   You don't have to wait for your favorite music stars to come to
your hometown to see them. 'N Sync, Britney Spears and TLC will
perform live at 8 p.m. Saturday at Nickelodeon's 12th Annual Kids'
Choice Awards. Since March 13, more than 4.5 million votes have
been cast by kids online for their favorite movies, TV shows, music
and sports stars. You'll find out who your peers selected as their
favorites on the night of the awards.
</P>
<P>
   Other stars you will see include: Mase, Ben Savage, Jonathan
Taylor Thomas, Kel Mitchell, Keyshawn Johnson, Tara Lipinski and
``Macho Man'' Randy Savage.
</P>
