<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LIZ-TILBERIS-EULOGY-ADVISORY-NYTSF </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following story, which has been culled from The New York
Times Syndicate's ``High Style and More'' fashion and entertainment
package, can be purchased as a ONE-SHOT by contacting sales
representative Debra Weydert by phone (732) 390-4480 or fax
732-390-4697.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LIZ TILBERIS: A GALLANT STRUGGLE ENDS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,900 words. OPTIONAL TRIM INCLUDED) &QL; 
 &UR; By SHARON EDELSON &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   She was the epitome of glamour, escorting Princess Diana to the
Costume Institute gala at the Metropolitan Museum of Art in 1996.
But beneath the velvet and satin, Liz Tilberis was fighting the
battle of her life. On Wednesday, April 21, at Mount Sinai Hospital
in Manhattan, Tilberis, editor in chief of Harper's Bazaar, lost
her six-year struggle with ovarian cancer. She was 51 years old.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know anyone who's displayed the kind of courage that
she has in the last six years,'' Calvin Klein said. ``To have
editorial meetings while she's having bone marrow transplants, and
be a wife and mother and run a fashion magazine while she's dealing
with this terrible illness is incredible.''
</P>
<P>
   In this tribute, friends, designers and co-workers remember this
very extraordinary woman.
</P>
<P>
   The article can be found in your system under the slug:
BC-LIZ-TILBERIS-EULOGY-NYTSF. It has been sent to category codes
``a'' general news, ``l'' lifestyle and ``e'' entertainment news.
</P>
