<P>
   &UR; KOSOVO &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times plans 2{ pages of stories, photos and
graphics on the continuing crisis in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MILITARY (Washington) _ Military developments on Kosovo.
By Elizabeth Becker.
</P>
<P>
   With map.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-RUSSIA (Moscow) _ Developments in Russia on Kosovo. By
Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-TROOPS (Washington) _ A look at the complexities of
assembling and deploying ground forces. By Eric Schmitt and Steven
Lee Myers.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-POWS (Belgrade) _ The Red Cross sees the three American
soldiers held in Yugoslavia. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-BELGRADE (Belgrade) _ Other developments in the Yugoslav
capital. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-JACKSON (Washington) _ Jesse Jackson is having a hard
time arranging for a trip to Belgrade to visit prisoners. By Susan
Sachs.
</P>
<P>
   We are considering, among others, stories on how the Yugoslavs
are getting oil, the plight of refugee children separates from
families and the impact on Europe of the Kosovo campaign.
