more severe than in most cities in the United States, and not
enough is being done to help, according to a new report on drug use
and its impact on the community. (800 words)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL &LR;  (``f'' code)
</P>
<P>
   AMEX-APPOINT (Undated) _ American Express's chief executive,
Harvey Golub, 60, says he he plans to retire in two years _ about
five years earlier than he had indicated in 1997. He will be
replaced as CEO by Ken Chenault, currently president and chief
operating officer. Golub will stay on as chairman for a year before
Chenault, 47, takes over that job as well. By Timothy L. O'Brien.
</P>
<P>
   EBAY-BUTTERFIELD (Undated) _ Ebay, the on-line auction company,
buys Butterfield &AMP; Butterfield, a California arts and antiques
auction house, in the news most recently as the auctioneers of O.J.
Simpson's belongings. The deal is a rare instance of an Internet
company buying its brick-and-mortar twin. By Saul Hansell.
</P>
