<HEADLINE>
`A BUG'S LIFE' SQUASHES THE COMPETITION 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``A Bug's Life'' _ There's a strong case to be
made that the best films last year were animated. And this one is
at the top of the heap. The insect characters are much more
sophisticated than many of their human counterparts. Disney has
wisely released it on the DVD format, as well as on VHS, and the
new technology brings the rich colors and art to brilliant life.
</P>
<P>
   ``Monument Ave.'' _ This tough-minded drama set in the rough
neighborhoods in Charlestown is a real eye-opener. No artificial
romanticism here as neighborhood loyalties, racial hatred,
organized crime, and ultra-violence plague the lean streets. And
Denis Leary gives a terrific performance.
</P>
<P>
   ``Elizabeth'' _ This is the Queen Elizabeth movie that should
have won the Oscar. Great performances, especially by Geoffrey Rush
and Cate Blanchett, and political machinations that would make
Marlon Brando's godfather tremble.
</P>
<P>
   ``Simon Birch'' _ Bring in Randy Newman. This sniveling, stupid
story is based on John Irving's novel ``A Prayer for Owen Meany,''
but they squeezed every bit of art from the book. A bad movie no
matter how you look at it.
</P>
<P>
   ``A Night at the Roxbury'' _ Chris Kattan and Will Ferrell
created some fairly funny ``Saturday Night Live'' sketches. But
they lasted just a few minutes. This movie seems interminable and
not at all funny. Re-rent a few ``SNL'' episodes instead.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Siege'' _ How many cliches can they cram into a dumb
movie? Dozens in this Denzel Washington-Bruce Willis-Annette Bening
fiasco.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: May 4: ``Babe: Pig in the City,'' ``You've
Got Mail,'' ``The Leather Boys,'' ``The Mummy'' (1932), ``Frank
Sinatra: The Best Is Yet to Come.'' May 11: ``Star Trek:
Insurrection,'' ``Another Day in Paradise,'' ``Velvet Goldmine,''
``As Time Goes By'' (BBC), ``Teletubbies Hanging Garden,''
``Bent,'' ``A Cool, Dry Place,'' ``Rowing With the Wind.'' May 18:
``The Imposters,'' ``Batman Beyond: The Movie,'' ``Bent,'' ``Holy
Man,'' ``In Dreams,'' ``Memorial Day,'' ``My Sweet Suicide,''
``Rowing With the Wind,'' ``Shadow of Doubt.'' May 25: ``Saving
Private Ryan,'' ``Gloria,'' ``Forbidden Fruit,'' ``Hellcab.'' June
1: ``The Base,'' ``Gunshy.'' June 8: ``From the Earth to the
Moon,'' ``Treehouse Hostage.'' June 22: ``Waking Ned Devine,''
``Sweethearts,'' ``Storm of the Century.''
</P>
