   _ An art gallery in Siegen, a German city near Cologne, is
planning an exhibit of 70 paintings by  &UR; Paul McCartney &LR; , who took
up the brush in 1982 but has heretofore been shy about showing his
work. ``I'm not out to show the world what I can do,'' McCartney
said in an interview two years ago when the subject turned to his
poetry. ``I think I've shown the world enough already.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's embarrassing really,'' he said of his paintings to an
interviewer last year. The Telegraph of London says that the German
gallery will probably charge an entrance fee of around $5.
