</P>
<P>
   G7-MEETING (Washington) _ The United States warned Germany and
Japan Monday that the world economy could not run for long on only
one engine _ an expanding American economy. But finance ministers
from the seven largest industrialized countries came up with no new
ideas about how to jump-start the other two. By David E. Sanger.
</P>
