<P>
   NATO-KOSOVO (Washington) _ The head of NATO's military arm says
the alliance will not use force in the Adriatic Sea to choke off
oil supplies headed to Yugoslavia. Even though NATO leaders agreed
Saturday to use warships in enforcing an oil embargo, German Gen.
Klaus Naumann, who heads the alliance's military advisory group,
says warning shots will not be fired at freighters. By ERIC
ROSENBERG. (Already filed.)
</P>
