   KOSOVO-NATO (Washington) _ The Pentagon announces the initial
call-up of Air Force Reserves to help in NATO refueling operations
amid the first serious signs of a split in the Yugoslav leadership.
Alliance officials say they are encouraged by Deputy Premier Duk
Draskovic's comments calling on President Slobodan Milosevic to end
his ``intransigence'' on the Kosovo issue. By GREG McDONALD.
(Already filed.)
</P>
