<HEADLINE>
AD FINALIST TO INTERVIEW ON CAMPUS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ William E. Lide, one of five finalists for the
athletic director position at Cal State Northridge, visits campus
today for interviews with the school's administration and an open
public forum.
</P>
<P>
   Lide, the director of intercollegiate athletics at North
Carolina Central, is available to answer questions from 4:30 to
5:30 p.m. in the athletic department conference room.
</P>
<P>
   Before taking the job at North Carolina Central, Lide was the
athletic director at Salisbury State (Md.) from 1987-93 and West
Chester University (Pa.) from 1993-95. He earned a degree in
physical education from Johnson C. Smith University in Charlotte,
N.C., in 1973 and a master's of education from UNC-Charlotte in
1976.
</P>
<P>
   The next finalist, Myles P. Corrigan, an assistant athletic
director at Washington, interviews Thursday.
</P>
