<HEADLINE>
THREE RING'S SPEED TO TEST THE DERBY COLTS 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 By JOSEPH DURSO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOUISVILLE, Ky. _ With only two days left before the draw for
the Kentucky Derby, only one filly on the backstretch at Churchill
Downs remained an announced candidate Monday to challenge the 19
best 3-year-olds in America in a race that only three fillies have
won in 124 years.
</P>
<P>
   She is Three Ring, who has won five of her eight starts but has
never raced against colts. And in the big leagues of horse racing,
few places are more exclusive than the starting gate at Churchill
Downs on Derby Day, especially for a filly: Only 36 have made it
that far, and none have reached the winner's circle in the last 11
years.
</P>
<P>
   But this year, no truly dominant 3-year-old colt has surfaced,
and the gates to the Derby are being besieged by traveling horses,
mystery horses and 30-1 long shots. And one star-gazing owner has
been willing to put up the $36,000 in entry fees to get his prize
filly into the gate: Barry Schwartz, the longtime friend and
business partner of Calvin Klein, the fashion designer, and a
trustee of the New York Racing Association.
</P>
<P>
   Three Ring galloped a mile and a half this morning over the
Churchill Downs track, but she was accompanied by some Derby
intrigue. Would she, in fact, be the only filly entered on
Wednesday? Or would she be joined by a filly from the richly
stocked barn of Bob Baffert?
</P>
<P>
   Baffert has won the last two runnings of the Derby and may be
starting the favorites this year, General Challenge and Prime
Timber. He also has the favorite for the Kentucky Oaks for fillies
the day before, Silverbulletday. He also trains Excellent Meeting,
another prize filly, who will probably run in the Oaks but may be
switched instead to run in the Derby as half of a powerful entry
with General Challenge.
</P>
<P>
   But Schwartz says that regardless of the competition, he will
face the Derby fire with Three Ring, a chestnut daughter of
Notebook and the mare My Nichole. She is a striking horse, with
$653,000 in earnings.
</P>
<P>
   ``She is so special,'' he said the other day, ``that they
recently postponed the construction work at Calder in Florida for
one week so that she could work out there.''
</P>
<P>
   Three Ring came up to Churchill Downs last week from Calder, not
from Gulfstream Park, where she raced into prominence last winter
by winning two big stakes for fillies. She had raced with
distinction as a 2-year-old by winning three of her five starts,
and even finished third in the Breeders' Cup Juvenile Fillies last
November behind Silverbulletday and Excellent Meeting.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know if she'll be the only filly in the Derby,''
Schwartz said of Three Ring. ``But I think she couldn't be any
better. I wouldn't be in it if she weren't special.''
</P>
<P>
   For a while at Gulfstream Park, it seemed likely that Three Ring
would test colts in the Florida Derby, particularly after a
powerful performance against fillies in February, when she blitzed
the field in winning the Davona Dale by nearly 15 lengths. But
after Three Ring drew an outside post for the Florida Derby, making
an already tough task tougher, Schwartz and the trainer Eddie Plesa
Jr. decided to hold her out of the race. Instead, they placed her
in the March 16 Bonnie Miss, which she won by more than six
lengths.
</P>
<P>
   ``The filly ran two phenomenal races, three weeks apart,''
Schwartz said. ``She showed that she's just as fast as these
colts.''
</P>
<P>
   And suppose she draws the outside spot in a 20-horse Kentucky
Derby?
</P>
<P>
   ``Wherever I draw, it's OK,'' Schwartz said. ``We're paying
$6,000 to supplement her to the Triple Crown, and $30,000 to enter
her in the Derby, and that's OK, too. This filly has been real good
to me.''
</P>
<ANNOTATION>
   (STORY CAN END HERE. OPTIONAL MATERIAL FOLLOWS)
</ANNOTATION>
<P>
   Plesa, who has never had a horse in the Kentucky Derby, put it
tersely, ``We're committed to the Kentucky Derby even if we get
Post 20.''
</P>
<P>
   Many trainers agree that Three Ring is fast, but they have
doubts about racing any filly against colts, particularly in the
springtime. Later in the year, the fillies get bigger and stronger
and become less vulnerable. Colts tend to throw their weight around
the track, and even a fast filly can come unraveled. The only
fillies who lasted the mile and one-quarter and won the Derby were
Regret in 1915, Genuine Risk in 1980 and Winning Colors in 1988.
</P>
<P>
   ``Brilliant fillies can pay a lot of bills for a stable,'' said
Jimmy Jones, who won the Kentucky Derby eight times with his
father, B.A. Jones of Calumet Farm. ``But almost always, it's
better to run them against other fillies.''
</P>
<P>
   Schwartz said he doesn't think he has been smitten with Derby
fever, which happens to many owners at this time of year. He has no
intention of running Three Ring in the Preakness, the second race
in the Triple Crown, since it is just two weeks after the Derby.
</P>
<P>
   ``But I might run her in the Belmont in June,'' he said. ``She
could make a mile and a half.''
</P>
<P>
   But for now, Schwartz knows that he has a filly who can run and,
just possibly, stay the course against colts in America's most
prestigious and exclusive race.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'll tell you,'' he said, ``she's smart and gentle. And I
think kindness is important. Some horses aren't kind, and they take
it out on themselves.''
</P>
<P>
   FINISH LINES:
</P>
<P>
   After a week of generally dry weather, rain fell Monday and
caused some disruption in Kentucky Derby training schedules. Still,
there were some workouts, with the trainer D. Wayne Lukas getting
both Cat Thief and Charismatic on the track. Cat Thief ran five
furlongs in 1:02; Charismatic, recent winner of the Lexington
Stakes, was clocked in 1:02 4/5. Of Charismatic, Lukas said:
``There is no horse doing better than he is. Whether that equates
to 12th place, 18th or first, I don't know.'' Also sneaking in his
workout was Elliott Walden's Ecton Park, whose five-furlong run was
timed in 1:02.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
