<P>
   ``I mean, I wouldn't have been surprised if people had wanted to
spit on me or yell at me. But that hasn't ever happened. It has
been our blessing that this community has let us go on.''
</P>
<P>
   _GRETCHEN WOODARD, whose older son was one of two youths who
killed four classmates and a teacher in Jonesboro, Ark., last year.
</P>
