house where they claim gang activity took place. This working-class
city of 70,000, just southwest of Chicago, is drafting an ordinance
that would evict all gang members from Cicero and punish them if
they return, even to visit their families. The proposal, expected
to pass in the town legislature, would be the first gang-eviction
law in the country. (Steve Kagan/New York Times Photo)
