4-26 -- According to Hasan Hyseni, seen in a refugee camp for
ethnic Albanians who have fled the violence in Kosovo, Serbian
forces in Izbica, his Kosovo village, pursued a simple tactic.
``Every person they saw, they killed. Five here. Ten there,''
Hyseni said adding that he is one of the Kosovar Albanians who
discovered the butchery and helped gather the bodies and dig 151
shallow graves for the victims. (Joseph P. Albright/Cox News
Service)
