France, the Australian's transplant has progressed faster in some
ways than expected. (Microsearch/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) UNDATED -- April 26, 1999 -- SCI-RED-MAPLE, 4-26 -- From
top: buds, twigs and leaves from the red maple tree. The forests of
the eastern United States are turning increasingly red, and the
growing brilliance of color signals a historic change in the
ecological character of a vast region stretching from the Great
Lakes to the Atlantic and from Canada well into the South. (Naum
Kazhdan/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) IRVINE, Calif. -- April 26, 1999 -- SCI-AYALA-EVOLUTION.,
4-26 --Dr. Francisco J. Ayala amidst his grape vines. Ayala, a
former Dominican priest, present day wine-grape grower, art
collector, author of 12 books and 650 articles on genetics, and a
professor of biological sciences and philosophy at the University
of California at Irvine, is known in the science world as the
Renaissance man of evolutionary biology. (Darcy Padilla/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) NEW YORK -- April 26, 1999 -- INDONESIAN-WRITER-2, 04-25
-- Indonesia's greatest modern writer Pramoedya Ananta Toer, and
his wife, Maimoenah Thamrin. Toer, 74, is on his first visit to the
United States and his first trip abroad since 1959. Pramoedya's
story of suffering and survival after being imprisoned and silenced
for 14 years on the prison island of Buru are the theme of a
memoir. The ``The Mute's Soliloquy,'' is to be published in the
United States on Wednesday by Hyperion East. (Fred R. Conrad/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. -- April 26, 1999 --
INTERNET-GOVERNOR, 04-25 -- Gov. James S. Gilmore 3d of Virginia,
right, shakes hands with James L. Barksdale, the chief executive of
Netscape at the company's headquarters. As the worlds of politics
and high technology increasingly come together, Gilmore is a man
who would like to be at the nexus. ``I speak their language,''
Gilmore says. ``We're on line together.'' (Peter DaSilva/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- April 26, 1999 -- RIVAL-MAGAZINES-MEDIA,
04-25 -- David Granger, the editor of Esquire magazine, in his
Manhattan office. Esquire and GQ magazine, nominees for National
Magazine Awards this week, are rival men's publications headed by
former colleagues; Esquire by Granger and GQ by Art Cooper. Cooper
has called Granger's magazine ``unsubtle.'' (Ozier Muhammad/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) CUPERTINO, Calif. -- April 26, 1999 -- APPLE-RESURGENCE,
04-25 --Jon Rubinstein, second from right, leads the manufacturing
team responsible for Apple Computer's iMac machine. Other members
include, from left, Glen Miranker, Jackie Streeter, Mark Foster and
Greg Paley. Apple Computer has had a remarkable resurrection.
Eleven days ago, the company exceeded analysts' estimates in
reporting its sixth consecutive profitable quarter. (Thor Swift/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
