<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-26 21:43 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A4174 &Cx1f; taf-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-ELWAY-RETIRE-NYT &LR;      04-26 0759
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-ELWAY-RETIRE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NOW THE NFL IS LOSING A LEGEND
</HEADLINE>
   (nk) 
 By MIKE FREEMAN   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The National Football League is about to go where it has not
been in almost two decades _ to life without John Elway. First
Jordan retires, then Gretzky, and now football's No. 7.
</P>
<P>
   Elway, the Denver Bronco quarterback who is one of the most
athletic and productive players in league history, is expected to
make his retirement official on Sunday. Elway made up his mind to
retire several weeks ago after consulting with close friends and
then his family.
</P>
<P>
   ``I can tell you officially that we're going to do it on
Sunday,'' the team owner, Pat Bowlen, said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Elway delayed the announcement because of the shootings at
Columbine High School in the Denver suburb of Littleton last week
and because he had second thoughts.
</P>
<P>
   ``Absolutely, I'm retired,'' he was quoted as saying in Monday's
Denver Post. ``One of the reasons I held off saying anything was to
make sure it's what I would do.''
</P>
<P>
   Elway, who has worn a brace on his knee for the last several
years, added: ``I seriously considered coming back, but I just
couldn't make it because of my knee. I've never liked it when an
athlete says he's retired and then comes back. Once I've decided, I
am certain.''
</P>
<P>
   A number of factors apparently went into Elway's decision to
retire after 16 seasons. First, Elway, 38, felt his body was
beginning to break down. It is likely, for instance, that he will
need a replacement for his left knee, which was reconstructed
earlier in his career.
</P>
<P>
   Also, even though he was the most valuable player in Super Bowl
XXXIII in January, he missed all or part of six games last season
with hamstring, back and rib injuries. He took 10 painkilling
injections around his rib area in November in the wake of a brutal
hit.
</P>
<P>
   Second, Elway felt there was little else to prove. After losing
three Super Bowls with Denver under the former coach Dan Reeves,
Elway won two straight with Mike Shanahan as coach.
</P>
<P>
   There was a time when Elway was concerned about his legacy, that
he would be seen as a quarterback with great individual statistics
but no championship trophies. But Giants Coach Jim Fassel, one of
Elway's closest friends, said, ``John doesn't have to worry about
any of that stuff now. There is no one who would challenge the fact
he is one of the greatest quarterbacks of all time.''
</P>
<P>
   The last factor for Elway was more personal. Elway wanted to
spend more time with his family, especially his wife, Linda, who at
the start of last season became critically ill after colon surgery.
</P>
<P>
   The NFL loses more than a quarterback when Elway leaves the
game. Like Michael Jordan and Wayne Gretzky in their sports, Elway
was an ambassador for football who became heavily involved in
charity work in the Denver area and across the country. He never
embarrassed the league with any off-the-field incidents.
</P>
<P>
   In recent years, friends of the quarterback said that Elway
often contemplated how many titles he would have won if Shanahan
had been his coach throughout his professional career. Elway had a
rocky relationship with Reeves, but was close to Shanahan.
</P>
<P>
   Elway leaves the game as the quarterback with the most
victories, 148. Elway had 47 game-winning or game-tying
fourth-quarter drives.
</P>
<P>
   Elway finishes with 51,475 passing yards, and he and Miami's Dan
Marino (58,913) are the only two quarterbacks to amass more than
50,000. Elway, Marino and Fran Tarkenton are the only quarterbacks
to throw more than 300 touchdown passes.
</P>
<P>
   ``With his arm strength and mobility, he was a rare combination
of talents,'' New York Jets Coach Bill Parcells said Monday at the
media day for the Cadillac-NFL Golf Classic at the Upper Montclair
Country Club in Clifton, N.J. ``I don't know if I've seen a
quarterback who had the ability to run and the ability to throw in
one package like John Elway.
</P>
<P>
   ``He is certainly a player that will be missed in the NFL. He
was a great asset to our league.''
</P>
<P>
   It is hard to imagine the Broncos truly replacing Elway, but
they will try with Elway's backup last year, Bubby Brister. The
good news for Denver is that Brister was 4-0 in the games Elway
missed last season. The bad news is that Brister turns 37 in August
and has not started more than eight consecutive games since 1990.
</P>
<P>
   Shanahan is considered one of the best offensive strategists in
the NFL, but few believe even he can make Brister into an elite
quarterback who is even one-fifth of what Elway was.  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
