<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 
Monday, April 26 JASPER-SLAYING (Beaumont, Texas) _ In a surprise development
Monday, the prosecutor and defense attorneys involved in the second
capital murder trial in the brutal dragging death of a black man
agreed on moving the trial, possibly to the Central Texas town of
Georgetown. The prosecutor and defense attorneys also want to reset
the trial for July instead of May 17. Other potential trial sites
being considered are New Braunfels and Kerrville, small towns also
near the state capital of Austin. By RICHARD STEWART. 
 
 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 

<TEXT>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
