<HEADLINE>
FOR A BRASSY, SASSY SPRING 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Usually, spring brings out pastels, but this year colors are
bright. Orange, hot pink, turquoise and red are cheerful antidotes
to winter's black and gray.
</P>
<P>
   Consider a tank top ($58) and cardigan ($85) in turquoise or
orange from the Bergdorf Goodman collection; a tangerine shift
dress by CK Calvin Klein ($195); a plastic ``straw'' bag in pink,
red and yellow by Antik Batik ($45); turquoise pumps with red
patent heels and red ankle straps by Manolo Blahnik ($455), or a
tangerine parka by Michael Kors ($795). All at Bergdorf's.
</P>
<P>
   Barneys New York has pink trousers by Helmut Lang ($365); orange
pull-on pants by Ronaldus Shamask ($600), and a sundress in orange
and red with pink trimming by Mark Whitaker ($425).
</P>
<P>
   Flower-embroidered straw bags by Rafe ($135), Kate Spade ($225)
and Lulu Guinness ($125) are at Neiman Marcus. And embroidered
fuchsia chiffon evening bags by Camilla Ridley ($328) are at Henri
Bendel.
</P>
</TEXT>
