<HEADLINE>
SHORT ITEMS ON TRAVEL DEALS  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, MAY 2) 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 By JOSEPH SIANO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   STEAMBOAT SAVINGS For passengers who place a deposit of $300 a
person by June 30, the Delta Queen Steamboat Co. will include
various discounts on five- to seven-night cruises departing Nov. 21
through Dec. 23.
</P>
<P>
   Most of the six cruises _ on the Delta Queen, American Queen or
Mississippi Queen _ begin and end in New Orleans. The discounts
range from 40 percent to a two-for-one deal to a 50 percent
companion fare, depending on choice of itinerary.
</P>
<P>
   The 40 percent discount, for example, on a Dec. 10 to 15 voyage
from Memphis to Nashville brings the fare down to $834 a person,
double. Among the trips: a stop in Galveston, Texas, for Dickens on
the Strand, a Victorian holiday festival, and a Christmas cruise on
the lower Mississippi. Call (800) 543-1949 or a travel agent.
Availability of cabins under this offer is limited. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NORTH AMERICAN RAIL Amtrak and VIA Rail Canada are selling
30-day passes good for unlimited coach travel on their combined
network of over 28,000 miles and 900 destinations. Travel must
include one segment in each country; reservations are required, and
pass holders must pick up a ticket for each leg. From June 1 to
Oct. 15, the price is $645. There is a 10 percent discount for
travelers 60 or older, children 2 to 18 traveling with at least one
adult paying full fare or college students with a Student Advantage
Card. Information: (800) 722-6137 or a travel agent. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SPRING DRIVE Kemwel Holiday Autos will offer a different sort of
upgrade on its European weekly rentals this spring and summer: Book
a car in one price category by June 30 and get it for the price of
the category just below it. Rates for one week (with unlimited
mileage) vary by country: the lowest is $79 in Germany, up to $129
in Britain. These rates are for cars similar to a Ford Aspire or
Geo Metro, with a manual shift. Tax, insurance and airport-pickup
fees are extra. See a travel agent or contact Kemwel at (800)
678-0678 or www.kemwel.com. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MILES AND MORE Shangri-La Hotels and Resorts give members of
Northwest's World Perks 500 miles a night on any non-discounted
rate, 500 miles on any suite stay or double miles on any
corporate-rate stay. All through May 31.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, individual Shangri-La hotels have specials. The one
in Singapore, for example, is celebrating a major makeover with its
Reborn Package: rates in the redone Tower Wing start at $134,
single or double, down from $237, and includes full breakfast.
</P>
<P>
   Good through June 30. The Shangri-La Golden Flower Hotel in
Xian, China, has a Xian Exotic Package with three nights, daily
full breakfast, round-trip airport transfers and two days' guided
tours of the city, the eastern starting point of the Silk Road.
</P>
<P>
   Rates start at $218 a person, double, for a superior room. Good
to Aug. 31. Call (800) 942-5050 or www.shangri-la.com.
</P>
