<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-BRAVES27-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Braves get two in 9th to finish trip at 8-3
 &HT;    By Carroll Rogers
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI _ The Braves have been through everything else this road
trip _ rain-out, snow-out, a 20-5 pummeling, a 12-inning marathon
in Los Angeles, East Coast, West Coast, a mile high and sea level.
</P>
<P>
   So why not something a little out of the ordinary Monday night,
the last of the 15-day adventure.
</P>
<P>
   Like the knuckleball. And a failed squeeze play that didn't fail
after all.
</P>
<P>
   Dennis Springer, the Marlins' fifth starter, was floating it the
Braves' way, keeping them off balance for most of the game, before
Atlanta scored twice in the ninth inning to beat Florida 5-3.
</P>
<P>
   Walt Weiss' RBI single broke a 3-3 tie in the ninth, and Andruw
Jones scored another run when he escaped a rundown with the help of
a Marlins misplay after a botched suicide squeeze.
</P>
<P>
   Rudy Seanez got the last four outs for his second save as the
Braves completed an 8-3 road trip.
</P>
<P>
   Springer, 34, making his first career start against the Braves,
had lost each of his first three starts, allowing three, four and
five runs. He puzzled most of the Braves through 7 1/3 innings, but
not their two natives of Curacao.
</P>
<P>
   Andruw Jones, who has used this trip to practice patience at the
plate and find his stroke, connected for a triple and a home run,
the latter a two-run shot in the seventh that gave the Braves a 3-2
lead.
</P>
<P>
   And countryman Randall Simon started the seventh-inning rally
with a double to right center, his third hit of the game in three
at-bats.
</P>
<P>
   Kevin Millwood was looking for a lift in his fourth start of the
season, after allowing four runs in each of his first four starts.
He was much sharper in this one, allowing four hits in 7 1/3
innings and striking out seven.
</P>
<P>
   Millwood left with two runners on and a 3-2 lead in the eighth,
and reliever Mike Remlinger got the second out before giving way to
rookie Kevin McGlinchy. But McGlinchy walked pinch hitter Derrek
Lee and Kevin Orie to force in the tying run before Seanez got the
final out.
</P>
<P>
   Jones' second triple of the year, a line drive to right center
leading off the third inning, set up the Braves' first run. Otis
Nixon, hitless in his previous eight at-bats, drove him in with a
two-out chopper up the middle to give the Braves a 1-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Millwood was on his game from the start, holding the Marlins to
an infield hit and one walk the first three innings. His shakiness
resurfaced in the fourth when he walked Mark Kotsay to start the
inning, then gave up a triple by Todd Dunwoody to the right-center
field wall. Orie followed with a hard single up the middle, giving
Florida a 2-1 lead.Carroll Rogers writes for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
